\[
N = 60 \, \text{kN} = 60,000 \, \text{N}
\]
\[
M = 10 \, \text{kN} \cdot m = 10,000 \, \text{N} \cdot m
\]

따라서:

\[
e = \frac{10,000 \, \text{N} \cdot m}{60,000 \, \text{N}} = \frac{10,000}{60,000} \, m = \frac{1}{6} \, m \approx 0.167 \, m
\]

